UserPKG
=======
![alt logo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dracolinux/UserPKG/master/res/hicolor/48x48/UserPKG.png)

Unprivileged package manager for Linux and NetBSD.

UserPKG is a convenient front-end for pkgsrc, simplifiying the installation and usage of third-party software for users.

Requirements
============

* Linux/NetBSD
 * Tested on DracoLinux
 * Tested on CentOS/RHEL 6
 * Tested on Ubuntu 14.04
 * Tested on NetBSD 6.1
* Build essentials

Status
======

Early Alpha.

Install
=======

Download latest release for Linux ([setup](https://github.com/dracolinux/UserPKG/releases/download/20140525/UserPKG-20140525-Linux64-Setup.tgz)|binary)/NetBSD, or build you own.

Build
=====

Requires Qt4 development files installed prior to building UserPKG.

```
git submodule update -i
cd DracoPKG/lib ; qmake CONFIG+=libpkgsrc CONFIG+=staticlib PREFIX=$(pwd)/../build  && make install
cd ../../ ; qmake PREFIX=/usr CONFIG+=libpkgsrc && make install
```

